First model: Budget and added revenue for actor, director, production, and distribution. These variables had the highest correlation with domestic total gross revenue. I used the square root transformation, so when analyzing the test results I needed to square the results to get the actual prediction. Not that while the coefficients appear to be 0, they are not actually zero - it is just that the values for budget and added revenue are so large that a one unit change has a small effect.
